\ncoupling. We also study the implications of the current data on the LFUV\nobservable $R_{\\phi}$, $Q_{4,5}$ along with $R_{K^{(*)}}$ in the high $q^2$. We\nfind that a precise measurements of these observables can provide a good\ndiscrimination between a few favored model-independent solutions, and have a\npotential to disentangle different heavy and light $Z'$ scenarios considered in\nthis work.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Mar 2022 17:17:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 4 Oct 2022 18:38:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-16"}
